<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib special">118. Harley, R. D. Artists’ Pigments c. 1600 - 1835: A Study in English Documentary Sources. 2nd rev. ed. London: Butterworth Scientific, Technical Studies in Art, Archaeology and Architecture, 1982. 236 pp. Index, bibl. ISBN 0-408-70945-6. </p><p class="annot">First published in 1970, this history of painting materials grew out of the author's dissertation research. The 1982 edition adds George Field's manuscript notebooks and color swatches, now at the Courtauld Institute of Art. The historical background of painting techniques and knowledge of technology of materials is documented by reference to important literary sources from Theophrastus, Vitruvius, Theophilus, medieval manuscripts, to Daniel V. Thompson and others. The book, with its comprehensive bibliography, is an important source for history of color use in painting. </p></div>
